00:00:02.919 --> 00:00:06.880
Hi, I'm Zach with Minka Aire and I'm here
at Del Mar Fans and Lighting to show you how

00:00:06.880 --> 00:00:10.450
to install the Minka Aire Concept ceiling
fan.

00:00:10.450 --> 00:00:16.980
Verify that you have all of the parts and
use the install manual as a guide.

00:00:16.980 --> 00:00:23.440
You will need the following tools; a Phillips-head
screwdriver, a straight slot screwdriver,

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:27.840
pliers, wire cutters, and a ladder.

00:00:27.840 --> 00:00:32.500
Turn the power off at the circuit breaker
box.

00:00:32.500 --> 00:00:38.589
Secure the hanger bracket to the ceiling outlet
box using screws, lock washers and star washers

00:00:38.589 --> 00:00:42.129
included with your outlet box and fan.

00:00:42.129 --> 00:00:47.429
Cut the fan wires 6 inches longer than the
downrod size you are using.

00:00:47.429 --> 00:00:52.679
Strip insulation off half an inch from the
end of each wire.

00:00:52.679 --> 00:00:58.619
Loosen the two set screws and remove the hitch
pin and lock pin from the motor coupling.

00:00:58.619 --> 00:01:04.150
Slide the wires through the motor coupling
cover, ceiling canopy and through the downrod.

00:01:04.150 --> 00:01:07.620
Thread the downrod into coupler.

00:01:07.620 --> 00:01:12.079
Set the hitch pin, lock pin and tighten the
two set screws.

00:01:12.079 --> 00:01:16.759
Lift the motor assembly into position and
place downrod into hanger bracket.

00:01:16.759 --> 00:01:22.620
Rotate until the check groove has dropped
into the registration slot and seats firmly.

00:01:22.620 --> 00:01:26.950
Insert the receiver unit into the hanger bracket
with the flat side of the receiver facing

00:01:26.950 --> 00:01:28.659
the ceiling.

00:01:28.659 --> 00:01:36.630
Connect the fan ground wire from the hanger
ball and hanger bracket.

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:42.729
Black wire to Black wire marked "To Motor
L" from the receiver.

00:01:42.729 --> 00:01:48.670
White wire from the fan to the White wire
marked "To Motor N" from the receiver.

00:01:48.670 --> 00:01:56.020
Blue wire from the fan to the Blue wire marked
"For Light" from the receiver.

00:01:56.020 --> 00:02:03.500
Black wire from the outlet box to the Black
wire marked "AC in L" from the receiver.

00:02:03.500 --> 00:02:09.460
White wire from the outlet box to the white
wire marked "AC in N" from the receiver.

00:02:09.460 --> 00:02:12.920
Secure all wire connections with plastic wire
nuts.

00:02:12.920 --> 00:02:18.580
Slide canopy over the 2 screws on the hanger
bracket.

00:02:18.580 --> 00:02:22.860
Rotate canopy in place and tighten screws.

00:02:22.860 --> 00:02:30.450
Insert the blades into the motor housing blade
slots, push blade until snug.

00:02:30.450 --> 00:02:36.830
Repeat process for each blade.

00:02:36.830 --> 00:02:41.480
Install one 100W medium base bulb.

00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:46.970
Raise glass shade up against bottom of fan
housing and secure it to the fan by twisting

00:02:46.970 --> 00:02:49.670
glass clockwise until snug.

00:02:49.670 --> 00:02:53.800
Leave a comment below and let us know what
you think of the Minka Aire Concept install.

00:02:53.800 --> 00:02:56.499
Thank you for joining me here at Del Mar Fans
&amp; Lighting.

